PRINCIPLED ALIGNMENT

The Principled alignment is the highest good in the Palladium world.

A Principled character believes in truth, justice, and the law as tools for
protecting the innocent.  They will not lie, cheat, steal, or harm the
innocent regardless of the benefit to themselves.  They are bound by their
word and their oath, and will go out of their way to help those in need.

GUIDELINES:
- Will not lie or deceive, even to enemies
- Will not break the law, even unjust ones (will work to change them instead)
- Will not harm innocents or bystanders under any circumstance
- Will help those in need even at personal risk
- Will keep every promise made
- Will not use extreme force when it is not warranted

Principled characters tend to be the classic heroes of Rifts Earth: the
Coalition soldier who refuses orders to fire on civilians, the Cyber-Knight
who upholds the old code of honor, the wilderness guide who helps refugees
flee the coming darkness.

Characters with this alignment command the respect of good-aligned beings
and are trusted completely by those who know them.  Their inflexibility can
be a disadvantage in the morally ambiguous Rifts world.

See also: scrupulous, unprincipled, anarchist, miscreant, aberrant, diabolic
